Vcenter
1. Login to the vSphere remote admin page
2. Go to upgrades on the left hand menu
3. Select the latest update and then install it

ESXI
1. SSH in the appliacne as root
2. Enter " esxcli software profilr update -p" the version that you want to update to "-d" 
the URL to get it

Alt
1.  Mount the ISO
2.  SSH into vCenter
3.  Run "software-packages install --iso --acceptEulas"
4.  Run "shutdown reboot -r updating"

ESXI
1.  Depending on the ESXI version, a usb with ISO installer can be used at boot to upgraded the existing installtion.
